<Requirements version="1" hierarchy="LLR">
  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Loop Component</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The robot shall implement an autonomous exploration loop consisting of data acquisition, localisation, mapping, decision making, and motion command generation, repeating until a termination condition is reached (maze fully explored or external stop).</Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier-based Exploration Strategy</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The robot shall implement frontier-based exploration by selecting adjacent unknown cells, computing a frontier score, and choosing the highest-scoring frontier as the next target; it shall avoid revisiting explored areas and update the exploration loop accordingly.</Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Completion Criteria</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The robot shall determine exploration completion when all reachable frontiers have been resolved or mapped; it shall provide a measurable progress indicator and stop when completion or an external stop condition is reached.</Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1.4">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Logging and Monitoring</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-1.1.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>The robot shall log exploration state, including current position, explored cells, time, and map version; shall persist logs in memory and optionally to non-volatile storage; shall expose an API to query status and progress.</Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-WALL-1.2.1">
