  </Justification>

  <Implementation>
    <FindingID>LLR--1--2</FindingID>
    <Solution>In LL-EXPL-1.1.1, removed the DependsOn LL-EXPL-1.1.2 to break the cycle. LL-EXPL-1.1.2 retains its dependency on LL-EXPL-1.1.1 and continues to refine HL-EXPL-1.1. This establishes a one-way dependency path: LL-EXPL-1.1.2 -> LL-EXPL-1.1.1, avoiding cyclic references. Updated traceability matrices accordingly and documented the corrective action. Implemented a plan to introduce automated ID validation and cycle-detection checks in the CI/CD pipeline to prevent future regressions. Architecture design can proceed with an acyclic LL requirement graph.</Solution>
  </Implementation>
